Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.35,0:01:48.29,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,110)}Ep. 23 - Your Name is Little
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.20,0:02:10.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor. Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.21,0:02:12.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did Lucy stop by here, by any chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.49,0:02:18.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Deighton!\NWhere did Lucy go?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.25,0:02:21.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Uh? Ah, Ben went out, alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.99,0:02:24.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about Ben, where is Lucy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.82,0:02:26.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.29,0:02:28.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May came a little while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.49,0:02:31.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And then went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.03,0:02:32.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Together with Ben?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.90,0:02:37.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh... Ben left way before she did.\NAlso took with him the puppy that was sleeping there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.90,0:02:41.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry I woke you up, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.46,0:02:42.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.42,0:02:46.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing how you're still awake,\Nit's probably not that late into the night yet. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.05,0:02:46.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.44,0:03:00.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose our brick-making venture didn't succeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.51,0:03:10.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought, a complete failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.69,0:03:13.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's strange that dad isn't here either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.30,0:03:17.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.69,0:03:20.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.00,0:03:23.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.80,0:03:27.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy! Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.40,0:03:34.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's turn back, Lucy-May.\NBen isn't here either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.48,0:03:37.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I wanna search more in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.75,0:03:39.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can't, Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.32,0:03:41.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A lady can't be wandering alone in the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.72,0:03:46.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But if we stop, Ben might abandon that baby dog\Nsomewhere and we won't know! 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.90,0:03:49.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That is not a baby dog, but a baby dingo. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.99,0:03:52.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I told you from the very beginning\Nwe should abandon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.42,0:03:55.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No! I'll never forgive myself for abandoning it! 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.90,0:03:58.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna keep that baby dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.02,0:04:00.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.13,0:04:01.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,See? We need to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.62,0:04:03.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate came here to look for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.99,0:04:13.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben, don't abandon the pup.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.80,0:04:16.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I beg you with all my heart not to abandon it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.30,0:04:29.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.49,0:04:32.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe the aborigines congregated somewhere nearby? 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.50,0:04:42.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At that, little one, I'm leaving you\Nto live around here, so take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.10,0:04:49.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still just a baby, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:54.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But if I were to bring you home now,\Nwe'd be in even bigger trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.61,0:04:59.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're a baby dingo, when you grow up,\Nyour ferocity may wake up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.29,0:05:05.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And then, even you would start wanting to butcher the sheep and poultry, which we people are keeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.07,0:05:08.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When that happens,\Nwe won't be able to keep you anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.90,0:05:12.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not just that, we'll have no choice\Nbut to kill you with our own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.70,0:05:16.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And that's not something I would be able to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.00,0:05:21.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye now. Feel free to stay in the woods,\Nor to run off to the prairies of faraway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.42,0:05:23.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just make sure you get as far from people as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.19,0:05:26.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? Leave now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.99,0:05:29.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.00,0:05:36.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. Then I'll have my leave first.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.80,0:05:52.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.13,0:05:54.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he have to be so damn cute?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:05:56.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.00,0:06:03.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look at who's the timid little guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.03,0:06:06.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're a baby dingo, remember?\NA baby of the dog that's nurtured in the wild!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.29,0:06:09.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like it or not, I'll have to leave you behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.18,0:06:12.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's look for a better place elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.06,0:06:23.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor! Doctor! Need you to wake up right now, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.70,0:06:24.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.99,0:06:29.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, where exactly did Ben go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.07,0:06:35.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, eh? Didn't you ask me\Nthe same thing a bit earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.50,0:06:39.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But you only said that Ben went out with the puppy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.43,0:06:42.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't Ben tell you exactly {\i1}where{\i0} he's going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.70,0:06:44.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, where did he go...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.50,0:06:49.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please, try to recall it, Dr. Deighton!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.83,0:06:49.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.18,0:06:51.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.07,0:06:54.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was as though he muttered,\N"Probably best in the forest". 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.71,0:06:55.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.63,0:06:59.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it! Ben left to dispose\Nof that baby dingo somewhere.
Comment: 0,0:07:02.41,0:07:05.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.02,0:07:08.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, Lucy-May?\NDoes your tummy hurt somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.79,0:07:10.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.03,0:07:12.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy wanted to bring up that puppy herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.66,0:07:13.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.32,0:07:17.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but alas...\NThat was a baby wolf, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:20.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all! It was a baby dingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.50,0:07:22.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing to do with wolves! 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.80,0:07:26.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I see, I see, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.11,0:07:29.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's nothing irreparable.\NAlthough it may not be the same dog,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.47,0:07:33.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,we'll find and catch another one.\NI would also set my mind to it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.50,0:07:35.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A normal dog would do just as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.39,0:07:39.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No! I wanna keep that one puppy and none other!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.76,0:07:41.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.10,0:07:46.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. Lucy-May, I never suspected\Nyou could be that uncooperative. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.52,0:07:51.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I want that puppy! That puppy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.00,0:08:03.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought, I need a kiln with temperatures\Nway higher than that for firing bricks well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.22,0:08:06.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, making your own bricks\Nand firing them at home is a fool's errand.  
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.88,0:08:12.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But then, the house for Ben and Dr. Deighton to live in\Nwould also have to be built from timber?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.70,0:08:15.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No. Right now, I'm considering simple dried bricks. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.60,0:08:16.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dried bricks?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.58,0:08:19.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. In other words, a house from dirt. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.21,0:08:21.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even that would be an improvement over the tent. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.74,0:08:24.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When the winter comes,\None would simply freeze in that tent. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.11,0:08:28.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tob is finally asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.74,0:08:29.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.76,0:08:31.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, but it's that late already?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.77,0:08:34.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are Kate and Lucy-May doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.06,0:08:36.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Probably waiting for Ben to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.55,0:08:38.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben is supposed to return?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.13,0:08:42.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Seemingly, Ben went\Nto release the baby dingo into the wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.25,0:08:44.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But they should be long asleep by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.49,0:08:46.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara, go see what's what. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.35,0:08:47.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.29,0:08:53.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.36,0:08:56.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Crying from learning\Nthat we'll have to abandon the baby dingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.24,0:08:57.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.30,0:09:02.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, we should be proud of that boy. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.67,0:09:03.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.52,0:09:05.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't even have to ask Ben for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.10,0:09:10.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He heeded closely to my sentiment\Nand left to get rid of that dangerous puppy himself.
